cli/test.md
     1Ôćĺ# The test command
     3ÔćĺWhen writing a book, you sometimes need to automate some tests. For example,
     4Ôćĺ[The Rust Programming Book](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/book/) uses a lot
     5Ôćĺof code examples that could get outdated. Therefore it is very important for
     6Ôćĺthem to be able to automatically test these code examples.
     7Ôćĺ
     8ÔćĺmdBook supports a `test` command that will run all available tests in a book. At
     9Ôćĺthe moment, only Rust tests are supported.
