cli/watch.md
     1Ôćĺ# The watch command
     3ÔćĺThe `watch` command is useful when you want your book to be rendered on every
     4Ôćĺfile change. You could repeatedly issue `mdbook build` every time a file is
     5Ôćĺchanged. But using `mdbook watch` once will watch your files and will trigger a
     6Ôćĺbuild automatically whenever you modify a file; this includes re-creating
     7Ôćĺdeleted files still mentioned in `SUMMARY.md`!
     8Ôćĺ
