     1Ôćĺ# Configuration
     3ÔćĺThis section details the configuration options available in the ***book.toml***:
     4Ôćĺ- **[General]** configuration including the `book`, `rust`, `build` sections
     5Ôćĺ- **[Preprocessor]** configuration for default and custom book preprocessors
     6Ôćĺ- **[Renderer]** configuration for the HTML, Markdown and custom renderers
     7Ôćĺ- **[Environment Variable]** configuration for overriding configuration options in your environment
     8Ôćĺ
     9Ôćĺ[General]: general.md
    10Ôćĺ[Preprocessor]: preprocessors.md
    11Ôćĺ[Renderer]: renderers.md
    12Ôćĺ[Environment Variable]: environment-variables.md
format/configuration/environment-variables.md
     1Ôćĺ# Environment variables
     3ÔćĺAll configuration values can be overridden from the command line by setting the
     4Ôćĺcorresponding environment variable. Because many operating systems restrict
     5Ôćĺenvironment variables to be alphanumeric characters or `_`, the configuration
     6Ôćĺkey needs to be formatted slightly differently to the normal `foo.bar.baz` form.
     7Ôćĺ
