format/mathjax.md
     1Ôćĺ# MathJax support
     3ÔćĺmdBook has optional support for math equations through
     4Ôćĺ[MathJax](https://www.mathjax.org/).
     5Ôćĺ
     6ÔćĺTo enable MathJax, you need to add the `mathjax-support` key to your `book.toml`
     7Ôćĺunder the `output.html` section.
     8Ôćĺ
     9Ôćĺ```toml
    10Ôćĺ[output.html]
    11Ôćĺmathjax-support = true
    12Ôćĺ```
    13Ôćĺ
    14Ôćĺ>**Note:** The usual delimiters MathJax uses are not yet supported. You can't
    15Ôćĺcurrently use `$$ ... $$` as delimiters and the `\[ ... \]` delimiters need an
    16Ôćĺextra backslash to work. Hopefully this limitation will be lifted soon.
    17Ôćĺ
    18Ôćĺ>**Note:** When you use double backslashes in MathJax blocks (for example in
    19Ôćĺ> commands such as `\begin{cases} \frac 1 2 \\ \frac 3 4 \end{cases}`) you need
    20Ôćĺ> to add _two extra_ backslashes (e.g., `\begin{cases} \frac 1 2 \\\\ \frac 3 4
    21Ôćĺ> \end{cases}`).
    22Ôćĺ
    23Ôćĺ
    24Ôćĺ### Inline equations ÔÇŽ
    32Ôćĺ### Block equations ÔÇŽ
