format/summary.md
     1Ôćĺ# SUMMARY.md
     3ÔćĺThe summary file is used by mdBook to know what chapters to include, in what
     4Ôćĺorder they should appear, what their hierarchy is and where the source files
     5Ôćĺare. Without this file, there is no book.
     6Ôćĺ
     7ÔćĺThis markdown file must be named `SUMMARY.md`. Its formatting
     8Ôćĺis very strict and must follow the structure outlined below to allow for easy
     9Ôćĺparsing. Any element not specified below, be it formatting or textual, is likely
    10Ôćĺto be ignored at best, or may cause an error when attempting to build the book.
    11Ôćĺ
    12Ôćĺ### Structure ÔÇŽ
    93Ôćĺ### Example ÔÇŽ
format/theme/README.md
     1Ôćĺ# Theme
     3ÔćĺThe default renderer uses a [handlebars](https://handlebarsjs.com) template to
     4Ôćĺrender your markdown files and comes with a default theme included in the mdBook
     5Ôćĺbinary.
     6Ôćĺ
     7ÔćĺThe theme is totally customizable, you can selectively replace every file from
     8Ôćĺthe theme by your own by adding a `theme` directory next to `src` folder in your
     9Ôćĺproject root. Create a new file with the name of the file you want to override
    10Ôćĺand now that file will be used instead of the default file.
    11Ôćĺ
    12ÔćĺHere are the files you can override:
    13Ôćĺ
    14Ôćĺ- **_index.hbs_** is the handlebars template.
    15Ôćĺ- **_head.hbs_** is appended to the HTML `<head>` section.
    16Ôćĺ- **_header.hbs_** content is appended on top of every book page.
    17Ôćĺ- **_css/_** contains the CSS files for styling the book.
    18Ôćĺ    - **_css/chrome.css_** is for UI elements.
    19Ôćĺ    - **_css/general.css_** is the base styles.
    20Ôćĺ    - **_css/print.css_** is the style for printer output.
    21Ôćĺ    - **_css/variables.css_** contains variables used in other CSS files.
    22Ôćĺ- **_book.js_** is mostly used to add client side functionality, like hiding /
    23Ôćĺ  un-hiding the sidebar, changing the theme, ...
    24Ôćĺ- **_highlight.js_** is the JavaScript that is used to highlight code snippets,
    25Ôćĺ  you should not need to modify this.
    26Ôćĺ- **_highlight.css_** is the theme used for the code highlighting.
    27Ôćĺ- **_favicon.svg_** and **_favicon.png_** the favicon that will be used. The SVG
    28Ôćĺ  version is used by [newer browsers].
    29Ôćĺ- **fonts/fonts.css** contains the definition of which fonts to load.
    30Ôćĺ  Custom fonts can be included in the `fonts` directory.
    31Ôćĺ
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
format/theme/editor.md
     1Ôćĺ# Editor
     3ÔćĺIn addition to providing runnable code playgrounds, mdBook optionally allows them
     4Ôćĺto be editable. In order to enable editable code blocks, the following needs to
     5Ôćĺbe added to the ***book.toml***:
     6Ôćĺ
     7Ôćĺ```toml
     8Ôćĺ[output.html.playground]
     9Ôćĺeditable = true
    10Ôćĺ```
    11Ôćĺ
    12ÔćĺAfter enabling editable code blocks, the `editable` attribute must be added to a
    13Ôćĺcode block to make it editable:
    14Ôćĺ
    15Ôćĺ~~~markdown
    16Ôćĺ```rust,editable
    17Ôćĺfn main() {
    18Ôćĺ    let number = 5;
    19Ôćĺ    print!("{}", number);
    20Ôćĺ}
    21Ôćĺ```
    22Ôćĺ~~~
    23Ôćĺ
    24ÔćĺThe above will result in this editable playground:
    25Ôćĺ
    26Ôćĺ```rust,editable
    27Ôćĺfn main() {
    28Ôćĺ    let number = 5;
    29Ôćĺ    print!("{}", number);
    30Ôćĺ}
    31Ôćĺ```
    32Ôćĺ
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    35Ôćĺ## Customizing the editor
    37ÔćĺBy default, the editor is the [Ace](https://ace.c9.io/) editor, but, if desired,
    38Ôćĺthe functionality may be overridden by providing a different folder:
    39Ôćĺ
    40Ôćĺ```toml
    41Ôćĺ[output.html.playground]
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
format/theme/index-hbs.md
     1Ôćĺ# index.hbs
     3Ôćĺ`index.hbs` is the handlebars template that is used to render the book. The
     4Ôćĺmarkdown files are processed to html and then injected in that template.
     5Ôćĺ
     6ÔćĺIf you want to change the layout or style of your book, chances are that you
     7Ôćĺwill have to modify this template a little bit. Here is what you need to know.
     8Ôćĺ
     9Ôćĺ## Data
    11ÔćĺA lot of data is exposed to the handlebars template with the "context". In the
    12Ôćĺhandlebars template you can access this information by using
    13Ôćĺ
    14Ôćĺ```handlebars
    15Ôćĺ{{name_of_property}}
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    41Ôćĺ## Handlebars helpers
    43ÔćĺIn addition to the properties you can access, there are some handlebars helpers
    44Ôćĺat your disposal.
    45Ôćĺ
    46Ôćĺ### toc
    48ÔćĺThe toc helper is used like this
    49Ôćĺ
    50Ôćĺ```handlebars
    51Ôćĺ{{#toc}}{{/toc}}
    52Ôćĺ```
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    80Ôćĺ### resource
    82ÔćĺThe path to a static file.
    83ÔćĺIt implicitly includes `path_to_root`,
    84Ôćĺand accounts for files that are renamed with a hash in their filename.
    85Ôćĺ
    86Ôćĺ```handlebars
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    90Ôćĺ### fa
    92ÔćĺmdBook includes a copy of [Font Awesome Free's](https://fontawesome.com)
    93ÔćĺMIT-licensed SVG files. It accepts three positional arguments:
    94Ôćĺ
    95Ôćĺ1. Type: one of "solid", "regular", and "brands" (light and duotone are not
    96Ôćĺ   currently supported)
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
format/theme/syntax-highlighting.md
     1Ôćĺ# Syntax highlighting
     3ÔćĺmdBook uses [Highlight.js](https://highlightjs.org) with a custom theme
     4Ôćĺfor syntax highlighting.
     5Ôćĺ
     6ÔćĺAutomatic language detection has been turned off, so you will probably want to
     7Ôćĺspecify the programming language you use like this:
     8Ôćĺ
     9Ôćĺ~~~markdown
    10Ôćĺ```rust
    11Ôćĺfn main() {
    12Ôćĺ    // Some code
    13Ôćĺ}
    14Ôćĺ```
    15Ôćĺ~~~
    16Ôćĺ
    17Ôćĺ## Supported languages
    19ÔćĺThese languages are supported by default, but you can add more by supplying
    20Ôćĺyour own `highlight.js` file:
    21Ôćĺ
    22Ôćĺ- apache
    23Ôćĺ- armasm
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    68Ôćĺ## Custom theme
    69ÔćĺLike the rest of the theme, the files used for syntax highlighting can be
    70Ôćĺoverridden with your own.
    71Ôćĺ
    72Ôćĺ- ***highlight.js*** normally you shouldn't have to overwrite this file, unless
    73Ôćĺ  you want to use a more recent version.
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    82Ôćĺ## Improve default theme
    84ÔćĺIf you think the default theme doesn't look quite right for a specific language,
    85Ôćĺor could be improved, feel free to [submit a new
    86Ôćĺissue](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/issues) explaining what you
    87Ôćĺhave in mind and I will take a look at it.
    88Ôćĺ
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
