guide/creating.md
     1Ôćĺ# Creating a book
     3ÔćĺOnce you have the `mdbook` CLI tool installed, you can use it to create and render a book.
     4Ôćĺ
     5Ôćĺ## Initializing a book ÔÇŽ
    32Ôćĺ## Anatomy of a book ÔÇŽ
    36Ôćĺ### `book.toml`
    38ÔćĺIn the root of your book, there is a `book.toml` file which contains settings for describing how to build your book.
    39ÔćĺThis is written in the [TOML markup language](https://toml.io/).
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    50Ôćĺ### `SUMMARY.md`
    52ÔćĺThe next major part of a book is the summary file located at `src/SUMMARY.md`.
    53ÔćĺThis file contains a list of all the chapters in the book.
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    73Ôćĺ### Source files
    75ÔćĺThe content of your book is all contained in the `src` directory.
    76ÔćĺEach chapter is a separate Markdown file.
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
